                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d573">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60 f 31/21: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Einstein</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-01-12T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1925—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. Your 35, September 3, 4 p.m.<note n="4" xml:id="d573fn4">Not printed.</note>
                    Your despatch No. 746, December 9. Does exchange of notes of December 5 require
                    legislative and presidential approval and publication? Department wishes to
                    publish in Treaty Series as soon as all Czechoslovak formalities are completed.
                    Your omission of “indefinitely” approved.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
